# stack-riverpod — Riverpod 2.x

## What it is

Compile-safe state management for Flutter. Successor to Provider.

## When I choose it

Any Flutter app past a single screen.

## When I avoid it

A 3-screen demo where Provider suffices.

## Conventions I follow

- @riverpod codegen annotation everywhere.
- AsyncNotifier for any async data source.
- autoDispose by default; opt out with .keepAlive() explicitly.
- ref.watch / ref.read appropriate to context (watch in build, read in callbacks).
- select() for rebuild granularity.
- Provider-based DI for repositories — never service locators.

## Common gotchas

- ref.read in build() = race conditions and stale data. Use watch.
- StateProvider is anti-pattern for anything complex — promote to Notifier.
- Family providers + autoDispose interaction is tricky — read the docs twice.

